text.section:
The Department of Corrections may, during the prisoner's period of incarceration in the county jail, take custody of the prisoner and hold that person in a state prison facility for the purpose of treating the following medical conditions:
Chronic heart and lung conditions;
Psychiatric conditions;
Acute medical conditions that require diagnostic testing or hospitalization;
Acute surgical conditions;
Pregnancy; or
Any other medical condition which the Department of Corrections may set out by administrative regulation.
